text: Frieda Szwillus (née Hennig;Älteste Frau Deutschlands stirbt mit 112 Jahren 30 March 1902 – 21 September 2014) was a German supercentenarian. She had been Germany's oldest living person from 22 April 2014 until her death almost 5 months later. She lived to be 112 years old and 175 days. Szwillus died in Raschau-Markersbach, Saxony, Germany. Szwillus was, at the time of her death, the second oldest German person ever behind Maria Laqua. == References == Category:1902 births Category:2014 deaths Category:German centenarians Category:People from Saxony-Anhalt Category:Supercentenarians
